# Diode

> [!word] Diode
> A uni-directional semi-conducting component
>
> A diode is a device that only allows _[[61-Archive/20220408104411-current|Current]]_ to flow in _one direction_.

> [!example]
>
> An [[19700101080000-Light-Emitting-Diode|LED]] (light-emitting diode) is a diode that emits light when [[61-Archive/20220408104411-current|current]] flows through it

## Analogy of a Diode

![[Pasted-image-20220413121232.png|Pasted image 20220413121232]]
A diode is like a **blood vessel**, for a specific direction, the valve opens, and for the other the valve closes.
好像那個魚鉤，有那個倒刺，不讓魚跑走那個。

## Inside a Diode

![[Pasted-image-20220415123942.png|Pasted image 20220415123942]]

- a diode is formed when P-type and N-type semiconductors are joined.
- A diode consists of two terminals.
- The positive terminal is the source of positive charge carriers.

## Characteristics of a Diode

- [[61-Archive/20220413125112-i-v-characteristics-of-a-typical-diode|I-V Characteristics of a Typical Diode]]
- It is important to have a [[61-Archive/20220408115601-resistance|resistance]] (typically $1k\ohm$) in [[61-Archive/20220411105450-resistor-in-series|series]] with a diode, otherwise the [[61-Archive/20220408104411-current|current]] can be very large.

![../60-Meta-Attachments/615d72bb8d84c0ae8b84079d9bd3958a.png](data:image/png;base64,)

The [[61-Archive/20220411123711-voltage-drop|voltage drop]] is caused by the “turn on voltage” (typically 0.7V) of the diode (the cost of using the diode)
